    {
      "id": "3b086fa830a9043bb8c525261aa38432401a2bd1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-04-12 20:35:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\nI was going to comment that the kernel still needs to handle the \"iopen\" mount option (by ignoring it) so that upgrading a 1.8 filesystem config that passes the \"iopen\" option at mount time does not cause a mount failure with a 2.x MDT.\n\nHowever, I don't see anywhere that handles the \"iopen\" mount option, even on 1.8, so maybe this is not a problem?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "16e59cf686ed7980a5bcff368c477c2f6717bfac",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-04-12 20:35:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI was going to comment that the kernel still needs to handle the \"iopen\" mount option (by ignoring it) so that upgrading a 1.8 filesystem config that passes the \"iopen\" option at mount time does not cause a mount failure with a 2.x MDT.\n\nHowever, I don't see anywhere that handles the \"iopen\" mount option, even on 1.8, so maybe this is not a problem?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c54350cf2847895c6042f4c88fc1b2ca7882dff0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-04-12 20:57:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe option that we use is called iopen_nopriv.\nIt and other related options are actually defined and handled in ext4-misc-rhel[56].patch",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
